JOHANNESBURG - The state capture inquiry will hear Parliamentary oversight related evidence on Monday. Chairperson of Portfolio Committee on Transport, Dikeledi Magadzi will first take the stand. WATCH: Makhosi Khoza pulls no punches Magadzi's testimony will be followed by former Chairperson of Portfolio Committee of Correctional Services, Vincent Smith and National Assembly chairperson for committees, and Associate Professor of Public Law at the University of Cape Town, Professor Richard Calland